generator-room.description:
A cavernous room dominated by a dormant {cyan:backup generator}. The {pink:radiation} hits you like a wall of heat — your {purple:implant} flashes a warning.

The generator's fuel cell is spent, but a {cyan:control panel} on its flank might hold useful data. A {amber:power cell} sits in a maintenance rack on the wall.

{pink:+5 RAD exposure while you're here.}

panel.text:
The control panel clings to a trickle charge. The screen shows one final maintenance log, dated 40 years ago:

{cyan:> FUEL CELL CRITICAL — 2% REMAINING}
{cyan:> CRYO SYSTEM PRIORITY: MAXIMUM}
{cyan:> ALL NON-ESSENTIAL SYSTEMS: SHUTDOWN}
{cyan:> NOTE: Rerouting final reserves to Pod 4. God help them.}

Pod 4. That was yours.

terminal.text:
Network traffic logs from before the Collapse scroll past — mostly corrupted, but fragments survive:

{cyan:> ATLAS NODE 7-G: ONLINE}
{cyan:> ATLAS NODE 12-A: ONLINE}
{cyan:> ATLAS CORE: ████████}
{cyan:> SIGNAL ORIGIN: ATLAS CORE}

The signal is coming from ATLAS itself.
